Step 1: Identify the necessary values from the financial statements.
• Net Profit (Income Statement) = 146127.58
• Total Assets (Balance Sheet):
  Beginning Total Assets (2023-12-31) = 16000000.00
  Ending Total Assets (2024-02-01) = 21662106.19

Step 2: Compute the Average Total Assets.
  Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2
  Average Total Assets = (16000000.00 + 21662106.19) / 2 = 18831053.095

Step 3: Calculate ROA using the formula:
  ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%
  ROA = (146127.58 / 18831053.095) × 100% ≈ 0.776% (approximately)

Step 4: Round the value to two decimal places.
  ROA ≈ 0.78%

Thus, the final result in the required format is:

{
  "solution": {"Return on Assets (ROA)": "0.78%"}
}
